{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=11226&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Urban Sustainable Planning Minor - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "The 20-unit minor in urban sustainable planning\u00a0focuses on the application of public policy, urban planning and public management to the analysis and solution of urban problems. It draws upon the interdisciplinary faculty and programs of the Price School of Public Policy and includes foundational courses that introduce students to the nature of urban phenomena and the analysis and solution of urban problems. The minor also introduces students to the professional and academic fields of either urban planning and development or public policy and public management. In addition, based on their specific interests, students have the opportunity to explore in greater depth three areas and approaches of urban problem-solving. This minor is appropriate for students interested in expanding their understanding of the fields of urban planning and public policy and management as potential professional careers as well as increasing their comprehension of the analysis and solution of urban problems.", "course": ["https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=169437", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=169481", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=170415", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=169435", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=169455", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=169456", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=170349", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=169475", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=169484", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=169485", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?