{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=11034&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Preventive Medicine (Health Behavior Research) (PhD) - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "The Department of Preventive Medicine, Division of Health Behavior Research, offers a degree program in preventive medicine (health behavior), leading to attainment of the PhD. The program is designed to train exceptional researchers and scholars in the multidisciplinary field of health behavior research. Students receive a thorough grounding in academic and research experience, encompassing theoretical and methodological training in such allied fields as communication, psychology, preventive medicine, biostatistics, public health and epidemiology. Students receive research experience by participating in projects conducted through the USC Institute for Health Promotion and Disease Prevention Research (IPR). The doctoral program is full-time: students are expected to enroll for fall, spring and summer semesters.", "course": []}
