{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=11293&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Orofacial Pain Certificate - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "The Certificate in Orofacial Pain is a hybrid program (face-to-face and online classes) with a total of nine courses (12.5 academic units), specifically designed for the practicing dentist who wants to improve skills and gain expertise to deliver the best care for patients with complex conditions. The certificate curriculum is designed with a series of didactic courses in which students will gain knowledge about the diagnosis, pathobiology and treatment of different oral diseases in the field of orofacial pain, including masticatory musculoskeletal pain, neurogenic orofacial pain, temporomandibular disorders, headaches, orofacial motor disorders including orofacial dystonias and bruxism, intraoral, intracranial, extracranial and systemic disorders that cause orofacial pain.", "course": ["https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171026", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171025", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171024", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171028", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171023", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171027", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171029", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171030", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171031"]}
