{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=12457&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Gender and Sexuality Studies (BA) - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "The Department of Gender and Sexuality Studies offers students the opportunity to examine the forces behind the cultural and historical production of gender, including their relationship to other factors including race, class, ability, nationalism and colonialism. The department aims for its students to develop competencies in critical thinking; research skills; community-engaged creativity and collaboration; feminist knowledge production; intersectionality; queer and transgender theory; justice, equality, and power; transnationalism; and decoloniality. The Gender and Sexuality Studies curriculum analyzes how gender and sexuality operate in politics, popular culture, the professional sphere, intimate life, health, technology, science, sports and the very production of knowledge itself. With this rigorous understanding of the shifting terrain of contemporary power relations, graduates will be able to identify, resist and transform oppressive systems in their personal and professional lives. The interdisciplinary major in Gender and Sexuality Studies will prepare students to enter graduate programs in the humanities and social sciences and in professional schools including law, business, education, and health care. In addition, the curriculum equips students for careers in industry, including the media, arts, communication, governmental and non-governmental organizations and public service.", "course": ["https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=162756", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=162757", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=162758", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=176478", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&c