{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=10389&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Fine Arts (MFA) - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "A two-year program administered in collaboration with the Graduate School, the Master of Fine Arts is a professional degree in the practice of art preparing students to pursue careers as professional artists. With an influential and innovative faculty and expansive facilities, the MFA program is one of the most ambitious, energetic and forward-thinking MFA programs in the United States. In addition to close, constant interaction with the faculty artists, students participate in regular seminars, lectures, discussions, and studio visits with leading visiting artists, critics, curators and theorists from around the world. The school's immersion in the contemporary art community is a critical component of the MFA program.", "course": ["https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160194", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160195", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160196", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160211", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=170056", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160198", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160199", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160200", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160208"]}
