{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=11316&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Design (MFA) - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "A five-term program administered in collaboration with the Graduate School, the Master of Fine Arts in Design is a professional degree in the practice of design. A progressive degree option is available on a competitive basis to current Roski undergraduate students. With a faculty of influential design professionals and an expansive, retrofitted building in the downtown arts district, the MFA Design program seeks to be an ambitious and far-reaching addition to educational design community in Southern California.", "course": ["https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171424", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171341", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171425", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171408", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171366", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171343", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171199", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171202", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171220"]}
