{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=10385&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Two-Dimensional Studies Minor - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "This minor is designed for students who wish to augment their understanding of art in general in two-dimensional areas, rather than complete a minor that focuses on one medium. This minor provides a broad scope of courses in 2-D media and studies. This minor is open to any USC student, especially those interested in animation to sharpen their drawing, color and compositional skills. Students interested in the vast varieties of digital visual communication can develop better color and compositional skills. Total number of units required is 24.", "course": ["https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171083", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171085", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171091", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171099", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171100", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171114", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171103", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171214", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171084", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171104", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171107", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171097", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171108", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171109", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171080"]}
{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=10384&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Sculpture Minor - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "This minor focuses on making, organizing and manipulating objects and their spatial relationships in a range of materials such as wood, fiberglass, clay, plaster, latex and metal. Course work includes choice of classes in sculpture, ceramics, visual literacy, public art, moldmaking, metal and casting. The three-dimensional skills taught in this minor intersect with many other disciplines including architecture, cinematic arts, special effects, engineering design, urban planning and any other areas where skills in maquette and model building are relevant. The total number of units required for the minor is 20.", "course": ["https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171088", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171106", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171111", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=176532", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171090", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=176678", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=176481", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=176482"]}
{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=10383&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Photography Minor - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "The photography minor provides an in-depth experience in all aspects of photography. The well-equipped darkrooms allow individual hands-on exploration of black and white and color processes, camera types, historical and traditional printing methods, lighting and film processing as well as digital technologies and issues. It also includes a foundation in photo theory and criticism. This minor is appropriate for students interested in an intense experiential exploration of the medium of photography. The total number of units required for the minor is 20.", "course": ["https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171091", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=176533", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171107", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171112", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=161651", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=161676", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171095", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171112", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171096", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171126"]}
{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=10382&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Painting Minor - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "Within both western and non-western traditions, painting has a long history as a site for aesthetic experience and cultural questioning. This minor allows students to immerse themselves in painting, as well as developing a grasp of the critical issues surrounding it. Foundation courses provide the fundamentals of color, composition, medium and drawing. Advanced courses require more ambitious projects, personal direction, research and sustained focus. Students majoring in many areas of the humanities may pursue this minor to augment their understanding of one of the key media in the arts. The minor is available to all USC students who wish to develop their painting skills. A total of 24 units are required for this minor.", "course": ["https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171083", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171085", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171100", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171214", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171084", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171104", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171097", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171109", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171080", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171126"]}
{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=12452&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Intermedia Arts Minor - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "This minor deals with technology in art making including digital photography, digital video and the Internet. Course work includes choice of classes in history of photography, digital media, visual literacy and computer imaging. The professional aspects of this minor assist students in developing careers in fine arts, communication, design, engineering, film, journalism and in any area where there is a need for flexible and creative imaging using digital media. The total number of units required for the minor is 20.", "course": ["https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171091", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171093", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171107", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171113", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171094", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171095", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171096", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171323", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171126"]}
