{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=11375&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Multimedia for Designers and Entrepreneurs Minor - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "Entrepreneurs, content creators and experience designers in today's tech-rich market environments must understand how multimedia arts platforms interconnect. Facility with state-of-the-art visual and audio tools, and the ability to combine and integrate them successfully to create compelling and persuasive experiences, is essential. The learning approach in this minor combines design-driven, user-focused theory with hands-on, practical tools and production skills. Within a studio critique model, technology fundamentals are combined with entrepreneurial and design thinking perspectives. These skills and techniques will augment and enhance the knowledge students learn in their home domains and majors, and in virtually any future field of endeavor.", "course": ["https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160283", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160286", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171226", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171835", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171837", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160284", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160289", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=170175", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171833", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171536", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160318"]}
{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=11378&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Product Design Minor - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "A minor in Product Design offers USC students a deep understanding of the design process leading to the creation of consumer goods and services, including the fundamentals of design thinking and human-centered design as they relate to successful ideation and implementation. Students will learn the method by which conclusions are made through study and application of acquired knowledge and skills in the areas of user research, market opportunity, consumer insights, competitive analysis, ideation, 3D form development, production methodologies, branding, packaging, marketing, and distribution. Course work will focus on the process by which decisions are made regarding not only a physical object's function and aesthetic qualities, but also if it is solving a problem, how it is solving that problem better than the competition, and whether or not it is a problem worth solving in the first place.", "course": ["https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160282", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171634", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171635", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171006", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=170909", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171834", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171833", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171836", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160318", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171536"]}
{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=12451&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Health Innovation Minor - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "The potential for innovation at the intersection of health, medicine, design and technology is exploding. In order to take full advantage of the entrepreneurial and research opportunities in this space, a new style of undergraduate education is necessary for a new generation of learners \u2013 agile and adaptive thinkers who cross easily from discipline to discipline, steadily advancing the role that technology plays in our present and our future. Because of their strong interdisciplinary foundations, the USC Iovine and Young Academy and the USC Keck MESH Academy are uniquely poised to take the lead in the design and implementation of such a curriculum, one that will provide the knowledge and skills necessary to succeed in the emerging field of health innovation.", "course": ["https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160280", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160282", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160287", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=176582", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=176677", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=169449", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=170909", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=176676", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171022", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=176692", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=176744", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=168229", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=168445", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=169448"]}
{"url": "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_program.php?catoid=11&poid=11374&returnto=3756", "type": "program", "title": "Program: Disruptive Innovation Minor - University of Southern California - Acalog ACMS\u2122", "description": "Disruptive innovation results from an invention or discovery that radically changes an existing eco or social system. Invariably, that change requires new learning and new, sustaining innovations in response. Lasting innovation, then, requires both creativity in generating fresh, bold new ideas and an understanding of the constant interplay of economic, technological, cultural and social forces that drive the use and consumption of products, goods and services. Innovators who maintain success and momentum over long periods have learned to anticipate and adapt to trends by focusing on the needs and opportunities presented by the customer, the citizen, the community and the user.\u00a0The\u00a0Iovine\u00a0and Young Academy utilizes the techniques of human-centered design and a uniquely interdisciplinary, hands-on approach to provide students with the knowledge and skills to understand, nurture and drive innovation. The course work in this minor delivers\u00a0a\u00a0range of fundamental theories, frameworks\u00a0", "course": ["https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160282", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160287", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160288", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=170530", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171833", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=170909", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=170175", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171022", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=160318", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=171536", "https://catalogue.usc.edu/preview_course.php?catoid=11&coid=167657"]}
